/**
By Gemini                                                                                                         │    
The existing launch.json is configured for Karma (which uses port 9876). Since this project uses the modern     │    
Vitest runner in Angular 21, I'll update it with more useful configurations for debugging both your             │    
application and your Vitest tests.                                                                              │    

I'll add:                                                                                                       │    
1. "Debug Tests (Vitest UI)": Opens the interactive dashboard.                                                 │    
2. "Debug Current Test File": A configuration that runs only the test file you currently have open in VS       │    
     Code.                                                                                                       │    
3. "Debug Application": An updated version for your Angular 21 app.                                            │    
                                                                                                                   │    
I've set up the launch.json file for your project with the following configurations.                              │    
To access these, go to the Run  and Debug tab in VS Code (Ctrl+Shift+D).                                          │    
                                                                                                                  │    
Available Debug Configurations:                                                                                 │    
1. Vitest: Debug Current File:                                                                                 │    
   * How to use: Open your test file (e.g., shopping-cart.integration.spec.ts) in the editor. Set a           │    
     breakpoint by                                                                                                       │    
         clicking to the left of a line number. Then, select this configuration and press F5.                     │    
        * Best for: Precision debugging. It will only run the test file you are currently looking at and will      │    
     pause at                                                                                                            │    
          your breakpoints.                                                                                        │    
                                                                                                                   │    
    2. Vitest: UI Mode:                                                                                            │    
        * How to use: Select this and press F5.                                                                    │    
        * Best for: A visual overview of all tests. It opens the Vitest dashboard where you can interactively run  │    
     and                                                                                                                 │    
         inspect tests.                                                                                           │    
                                                                                                                  │    
   3. Vitest: Debug All Tests:                                                                                    │    
       * Best for: Running your entire test suite with the debugger attached.                                     │    
                                                                                                                  │    
    4. Angular: Serve App (Chrome):                                                                                │    
       * How to use: Ensure your app is running (with npm start or ng serve) and then select this to debug the    │    
          application logic itself in a Chrome window.                                                             │    
                                                                                                                  │    
  Debugging Pro-Tip:                                                                                              │    
   Since you are using Vitest, the debugger works instantly with standard Node breakpoints. You can also use       │    
   console.log() in your tests, and the output will appear directly in your Integrated Terminal in VS Code. 


 I'll merge the original configurations back into the launch.json file so you  
  have both available. Note that the original ng test (Karma-based) might not   
  work with your current Vitest setup, but I'll keep it there as requested.  

**/
{
  "version": "0.2.0",
  "configurations": [
    {
      "name": "ng serve",
      "type": "chrome",
      "request": "launch",
      "preLaunchTask": "npm: start",
      "url": "http://localhost:4200/"
    },
    {
      "name": "ng test (Karma Legacy)",
      "type": "chrome",
      "request": "launch",
      "preLaunchTask": "npm: test",
      "url": "http://localhost:9876/debug.html"
    },
    {
      "name": "Angular: Serve App (Chrome)",
      "type": "chrome",
      "request": "launch",
      "url": "http://localhost:4200",
      "webRoot": "${workspaceFolder}",
      "sourceMaps": true,
      "userDataDir": "${workspaceFolder}/.vscode/pwa-debugger-profile"
    },
    {
      "name": "Vitest: Debug All Tests",
      "type": "node",
      "request": "launch",
      "program": "${workspaceFolder}/node_modules/@angular/cli/bin/ng.js",
      "args": [
        "test",
        "--debug"
      ],
      "console": "integratedTerminal",
      "sourceMaps": true,
      "smartStep": true
    },
    {
      "name": "Vitest: Debug Current File",
      "type": "node",
      "request": "launch",
      "program": "${workspaceFolder}/node_modules/@angular/cli/bin/ng.js",
      "args": [
        "test",
        "--debug",
        "--include",
        "${relativeFile}",
        "--no-watch"
      ],
      "console": "integratedTerminal",
      "sourceMaps": true,
      "smartStep": true
    },
    {
      "name": "Vitest: UI Mode",
      "type": "node",
      "request": "launch",
      "program": "${workspaceFolder}/node_modules/@angular/cli/bin/ng.js",
      "args": [
        "test",
        "--ui"
      ],
      "console": "integratedTerminal"
    }
  ]
}